1
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:14,833
<i>You went in for a checkup,
I heard.</i>

2
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:16,400
<i> Are you dying or something?</i>

3
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:18,267
<i> I'm not dying yet.</i>

4
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,100
<i> Don't get too excited.</i>

5
00:00:20,233 --> 00:00:22,400
<i>This is perfect timing
for calling us in, Miss H.</i>

6
00:00:22,533 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>I have something for you to do.</i>

7
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:24,867
<i> What is it, Miss H?</i>

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:25,767
<i> Dad?</i>

9
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,867
<i>I've already sent Diana's
number.</i>

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:28,800
<i> All right, Dad.</i>

11
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,300
<i> Is your mother there?</i>

12
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:31,267
<i> Manuel?</i>

13
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,767
<i> So, how was your checkup?</i>

14
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,033
<i> I'm strong.</i>

15
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,867
<i> I can't get sick.</i>

16
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,633
<i>You can only get sick
when I'm by your side.</i>

17
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:40,633
<i>Because I want to be
the only one taking care of you.</i>

18
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,200
<i> Just me. No one else.</i>

19
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:45,600
<i>All I wish for
is your peace of mind.</i>

20
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:48,200
<i>Forgive me for what I'm about
to do to your mom.</i>

21
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:53,000
<i>I'm going to have her put in
jail because of all her lies.</i>

22
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:15,100
Felma.

23
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,133
What are you doing?

24
00:01:21,967 --> 00:01:23,867
Are you preparing
for your death?

25
00:01:25,567 --> 00:01:26,700
Just to be sure.

26
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:35,033
What if your neurologist cousin
gets the same diagnosis?

27
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:38,967
And if my tumor needs
to be removed...

28
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:44,867
I need to prepare the kids
for whatever might happen.

29
00:01:45,967 --> 00:01:51,133
Felma, can you not entertain
that fear for now?

30
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,267
We haven't even done anything
yet,

31
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,600
and you're already thinking
about death.

32
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:59,400
Why can't you imagine the
surgery being successful?

33
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:01,733
That you recover...

34
00:02:01,867 --> 00:02:03,167
that you'll be happy?

35
00:02:04,267 --> 00:02:05,467
Listen to me.

36
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:10,167
I prayed last night.

37
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:19,900
I asked God to heal my tumor.

38
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:21,967
That it shrinks.

39
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,933
And if it has to be removed,

40
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:31,700
that the operation is safe
and not cancerous.

41
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:34,900
But while I was praying,

42
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:45,467
I realized that someday
I will have to leave them.

43
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:50,800
So I still need to prepare
them...

44
00:02:50,967 --> 00:02:52,733
The ones I'll leave behind.

45
00:02:52,867 --> 00:02:54,667
The house.

46
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,733
My bank accounts.

47
00:02:56,867 --> 00:02:58,600
My investments.

48
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:01,300
This. The FMP.

49
00:03:01,433 --> 00:03:05,533
I need to organize everything
so that anytime...

50
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:09,400
everything is ready.

51
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:13,867
So they won't end up fighting
over it...

52
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:16,633
when I'm gone.

53
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:19,400
Noah,

54
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:27,467
don't think I'm giving up on
this tumor.

55
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:30,000
I'm going to fight.

56
00:03:31,567 --> 00:03:33,100
We are.

57
00:03:33,233 --> 00:03:38,167
I'm just preparing
for what might happen.

58
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:44,533
I just want to secure
my children's future.

59
00:03:57,633 --> 00:03:58,767
I'm sorry.

60
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:03,767
I'm sorry I misjudged you.

61
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:09,067
I forgot you're not the kind
of woman who gives up easily.

62
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:17,533
You're the kind who always look
at hope, not defeat.

63
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,433
Everything you've been through
has made you stronger.

64
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,633
No matter how strong I am,

65
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:33,267
there are moments when I fall
apart.

66
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:35,900
And that's where I came in.

67
00:04:36,967 --> 00:04:41,567
To help you rebuild every part
of your life that collapsed.

68
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:46,233
Thank you, Noah.

69
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:58,900
From then until now, you never
get tired of pushing me upward.

70
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:09,733
Even when, most of the time,
you're left behind.

71
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:13,100
Overlooked.

72
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:19,100
I'm scared, Noah. I'm scared.

73
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:24,033
I am too.

74
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,767
I'm scared as well.

75
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,933
Don't worry.

76
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:33,733
I've already talked to Emil.

77
00:05:35,533 --> 00:05:38,667
He's coming here this weekend.

78
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:55,267
Did you find a promo fare,
Alice?

79
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,867
Yes, but it's not a direct
flight.

80
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,100
Manila, Hong Kong, then Calgary.

81
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,433
That's okay. Book it.

82
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:03,633
<i> Are you sure?</i>

83
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:05,467
How will you convince Manuel?

84
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,867
I'll handle Manuel.

85
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,100
I'll hang up now. Thank you.

86
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,733
You and Alice are traveling?

87
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:15,533
We are.

88
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:17,667
Taiwan, remember?

89
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:20,167
Didn't I already say
I'm not going?

90
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:23,233
Manuel, I'm trying here.

91
00:06:23,367 --> 00:06:26,833
I'm really trying
to fix our relationship.

92
00:06:26,967 --> 00:06:28,433
Meet me halfway.

93
00:06:29,567 --> 00:06:33,467
Can't you at least try?

94
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,933
Make some effort.

95
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:37,300
No, Hazel.

96
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:40,733
This is all we can ever be.

97
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,100
Living under the same roof,
just like we agreed.

98
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:48,133
So to you, this marriage
is just part of a deal?

99
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:51,000
Won't you even give our marriage
a chance?

100
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:52,033
No.

101
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,567
Hazel, from the very beginning,
you knew who truly had my heart.

102
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,733
This is as far as we go.

103
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:01,967
I'm still going home
to my family.

104
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:03,733
What?

105
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,267
What do you mean?

106
00:07:07,667 --> 00:07:09,667
What are you saying, Manuel?

107
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,700
You really want to know
the truth?

108
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,267
Yes!

109
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,967
Because I hate being kept
in the dark!

110
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,367
Here's the truth.

111
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,567
From the start,
I already had my doubts.

112
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:24,133
You paid Timo to frame Coleen.

113
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:29,967
That's why I got back together
with you to find out the truth.

114
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,367
You're unbelievable.

115
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:34,933
You'll never find any evidence
against me.

116
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:36,667
None!

117
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,233
Because it's not true.

118
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:41,133
It's not true!

119
00:08:05,533 --> 00:08:06,667
<i> Kenjie,</i>

120
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,133
how's the task I gave you?

121
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,433
It's done, Miss H.

122
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:11,267
We are already here at Timo's
house.

123
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,100
Good.

124
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:14,800
Don't mess this up.

125
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,400
Timo won't talk.

126
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:23,767
But someone might convince
his wife and mother.

127
00:08:23,933 --> 00:08:25,367
Don't worry.

128
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:29,400
After this, Becca and Diana
won't be able to speak anymore.

129
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,000
Who are you?

130
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:41,167
Shut up!

131
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:45,333
Let go of me!

132
00:08:45,467 --> 00:08:46,867
Hey! Stop that!

133
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,567
The police are here!
No one move!

134
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:57,400
Let go of me!

135
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:02,767
Let's go!

136
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:03,833
Miss Becca?

137
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:07,800
Miss Becca?

138
00:09:08,867 --> 00:09:10,200
It's okay now. You're safe.
It's over.

139
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:16,633
Thank you. Thank you so much.

140
00:09:17,667 --> 00:09:19,500
It's alright. You're safe now.

141
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:22,700
Thank you.

142
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:39,933
You two are stubborn.
You still won't talk?

143
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:43,000
Come on. Talk already!

144
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,667
Any news? Did they talk?

145
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,167
Captain, they still won't say
anything.

146
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,467
It's our turn.

147
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:03,000
Just tell us who ordered you
to put an end to this.

148
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:07,133
We already told you.
No one ordered us.

149
00:10:07,267 --> 00:10:09,000
We were just trying to steal.

150
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:10,800
Don't mess with us, kid.

151
00:10:11,967 --> 00:10:15,167
Of all the houses to rob,
you chose the Malabanans'.

152
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:18,533
One look and you'd know there's
nothing to steal there.

153
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:21,967
Then how do you explain
the gasoline and the lighter?

154
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:26,400
We'll tell you the truth, Sir.

155
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:27,567
Hey!

156
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,733
What truth?

157
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:31,633
No one ordered us.

158
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:33,133
We did it on our own.

159
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,500
I don't want to lie anymore,
bro.

160
00:10:36,633 --> 00:10:38,667
Let's just tell them.

161
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,400
Maybe we'll get off lighter.

162
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,833
Right, Sir?

163
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:46,967
Maybe. It's possible.
You could be our witnesses.

164
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:54,467
You're right.

165
00:10:56,133 --> 00:11:00,500
Someone ordered us
to scare Diana Malabanan

166
00:11:00,633 --> 00:11:02,333
and burn their house down.

167
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,467
Who ordered you?

168
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,600
Why is there so much food?

169
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:33,600
I'm celebrating my victory.

170
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:35,100
What victory?

171
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,800
Weren't you so smug last night?

172
00:11:38,933 --> 00:11:43,600
So sure that I paid Timo
to frame Coleen

173
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:45,400
for Jessica's death?

174
00:11:46,633 --> 00:11:47,633
Guess what.

175
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:52,967
You won't find a single piece
of evidence against me.

176
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,367
Nothing. It's over.

177
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,900
Really, Hazel?

178
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,833
Absolutely.

179
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:06,733
<i>Joel and I have been tailing the
men watching Miss Becca, Dad.</i>

180
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:08,600
<i> They're heading to the house.</i>

181
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,700
<i> Are the police already there?</i>

182
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:19,333
<i> Yes.</i>

183
00:12:19,467 --> 00:12:21,933
<i>We've already hid Diana
and the kids.</i>

184
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:23,367
<i> Everything's in place.</i>

185
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,167
What are you smirking about?

186
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:31,300
Nothing.

187
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:33,267
I just remembered something.

188
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,300
<i> Hello, Jeff.</i>

189
00:12:58,433 --> 00:12:59,500
<i> What's the update?</i>

190
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,700
<i> Dad, it's a success.</i>

191
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,533
<i>The police arrested the men.
Caught them in the act.</i>

192
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,833
Come on, Hazel. Let's eat.

193
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,600
Bacon. Do you want some bacon?

194
00:13:33,867 --> 00:13:35,067
Thank you so much.

195
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:38,533
How did you save my family?

196
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:42,433
They called me using
Diana's phone, son.

197
00:13:42,567 --> 00:13:45,367
They explained everything to me.

198
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:48,433
<i>We have a hunch they'll carry
out their plan tonight.</i>

199
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,167
<i> My God.</i>

200
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,100
<i> But don't worry, Miss Becca.</i>

201
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:53,567
<i> We're arresting them.</i>

202
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,967
<i>Colonel Sarabia also ordered
an entrapment operation.</i>

203
00:13:57,133 --> 00:13:58,167
<i> Wait.</i>

204
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,133
<i> Wait!</i>

205
00:13:59,267 --> 00:14:01,367
<i> What about my grandchildren?</i>

206
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:04,667
<i> They might get caught in this.</i>

207
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,333
<i> They won't.</i>

208
00:14:06,467 --> 00:14:09,933
<i>They'll stay at my condo
for now with Diana.</i>

209
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:12,533
<i>We've already discharged
her from the hospital.</i>

210
00:14:12,667 --> 00:14:14,767
<i>Miss Becca, please don't worry.</i>

211
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,200
<i> We'll make sure they're safe.</i>

212
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:21,800
So that's why there were men
watching our house.

213
00:14:21,933 --> 00:14:24,300
They really had
something evil planned.

214
00:14:24,433 --> 00:14:26,333
We've also informed
Colonel Sarabia

215
00:14:26,467 --> 00:14:28,567
that your life
is in danger here.

216
00:14:28,733 --> 00:14:31,667
If you notice,
the guards have changed.

217
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:33,467
They're investigating the
previous guards assigned here.

218
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:38,767
I don't know how to thank you.

219
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:45,367
I'll testify against Hazel Cruz
if you file charges against her.

220
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:55,767
Jeffrey, please ask your parents
to forgive me again.

221
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,933
For all my sins.

222
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,500
Especially against
Coleen Cruz...

223
00:15:02,667 --> 00:15:05,400
and most of all, Jessica.

224
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,667
Why isn't he answering?

225
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:40,633
I knew it!

226
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,267
What is it?

227
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,900
- Why?
- What now, Hazel?

228
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:51,867
You're such a liar!

229
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,767
All that talk about Taiwan,

230
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,533
when all you really wanted was
to bring me back to Canada!

231
00:15:59,200 --> 00:15:59,900
Oh, well.

232
00:16:01,233 --> 00:16:02,367
There's no point denying it.

233
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,700
Yes, Manuel.

234
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:07,133
We're going back to Canada.

235
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:08,000
We're going home.

236
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:10,300
I'm not going with you.

237
00:16:12,667 --> 00:16:16,600
Don't forget I'm a nurse.

238
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:18,433
I can heal you.

239
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:19,867
And I can also make you sick.

240
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,767
I'll do whatever it takes
to get you through the airport.

241
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:33,533
If I have to fabricate
medical papers

242
00:16:33,667 --> 00:16:36,967
saying you need surgery
in Canada, I'll do it.

243
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:43,700
I'll sedate you, so you sleep
the entire flight.

244
00:16:43,867 --> 00:16:45,233
You won't be able to fight back.

245
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:50,333
I'll hide you again, Manuel.

246
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:52,133
While I fix everything.

247
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:55,500
And this time,
no one will ever find you.

248
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:59,900
No one will rescue
you anymore, Manuel.

249
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:10,533
Someone will.

250
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,367
It's them.

251
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,433
It's open!

252
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:19,400
Come in!

253
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:24,867
Manuel!

254
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,633
Good afternoon.

255
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:29,967
We're here for Mrs. Hazel Cruz.

256
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:33,533
Why do you need my wife?

257
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,467
We'd like to invite her
to the police station.

258
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:40,233
Why?

259
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:42,067
Because two suspects have
identified her

260
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,633
as the one behind the attempted
kidnapping and arson

261
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:46,133
of the home of Diana Malabanan.

262
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:50,600
They said she gave the order.

263
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:15,367
Ma'am?

264
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:18,367
Wait a second.

265
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:20,900
Ma'am Felma.

266
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:22,233
Ma'am Felma.

267
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,833
Sir Noah is here.

268
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:28,133
Come in, Sir.

269
00:18:28,267 --> 00:18:32,100
You know, she hasn't been
able to get up since earlier.

270
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:33,800
Noah?

271
00:18:33,933 --> 00:18:34,533
Hi.

272
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:38,333
Didang!

273
00:18:38,467 --> 00:18:41,267
Why did you bring Noah here?

274
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,433
Ma'am, I was getting
worried about you.

275
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:47,100
You refused to go
to the hospital.

276
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:48,567
I thought maybe
if it was Sir Noah...

277
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:50,000
You're overreacting.

278
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:55,433
It's just a fever.

279
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:59,300
How would I know if it's
connected to your tumor?

280
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:04,400
I really regret telling
you about my illness.

281
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:06,333
***

282
00:19:06,467 --> 00:19:09,433
You're watching my every move.

283
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,133
You worry too much.

284
00:19:11,267 --> 00:19:14,033
But, Ma'am, didn't I tell you?

285
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:15,767
I promised you this.

286
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:20,633
I'll be the strong one for you,
and I'll keep your secret.

287
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:27,800
Noah, sorry about Didang.

288
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,800
We bothered you.

289
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:31,733
Felma, it's okay.

290
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:37,833
At least when I leave,

291
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:39,867
I know someone understands
your condition

292
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,633
and will look after you.

293
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:43,500
See?

294
00:19:43,633 --> 00:19:44,467
Are you leaving?

295
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:49,567
There's a problem with one of
Noah's Ark Builders' projects.

296
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:53,500
I need to go to Davao and
personally check on it.

297
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,400
When?

298
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:58,633
How long will you be gone?

299
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:02,367
My flight is tonight.

300
00:20:02,533 --> 00:20:04,600
But I'll be back this weekend.

301
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:06,667
This weekend?

302
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,267
That's so long!

303
00:20:25,067 --> 00:20:25,900
Ma'am, this way, please.

304
00:20:31,267 --> 00:20:33,000
You shameless people!

305
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:35,867
Shameless! Darn you!

306
00:20:36,033 --> 00:20:37,367
- Ma'am, please stop.
- You have no shame!

307
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:38,667
You shameless people!

308
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,367
What are you talking about?

309
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,433
You! What are you saying?

310
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:43,200
- That's enough, Ma'am.
- I didn't order you

311
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:44,367
to do anything!

312
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:47,733
What? Now you're dragging me
into your crimes?

313
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:49,967
We're just telling
the truth, Miss H!

314
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,133
You ordered us!

315
00:20:51,267 --> 00:20:52,800
Yes, you did!

316
00:20:52,933 --> 00:20:54,467
You liars!

317
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,867
You really want to...

318
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,900
- You're lying!
- That's enough.

319
00:20:59,033 --> 00:21:00,367
You have no shame! Do you think
you can get away with this?

320
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,867
- You think you can?
- That's enough.

321
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:02,967
- What?
- That's enough.

322
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:07,167
I will sue you,
do you understand?

323
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:08,567
I will sue you!

324
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:21,667
Ma'am, I'm glad you finally ate.

325
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,667
At least you can take
your medicine now.

326
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:30,133
Can you stay in Davao
for just two days?

327
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,500
Ma'am Felma is something else.

328
00:21:33,633 --> 00:21:34,800
So clingy.

329
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:37,933
It's not like that.

330
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:40,067
I'm just scared.

331
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:44,333
What if something happens
to me and Noah isn't here?

332
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,367
Ma'am, you're so stubborn.

333
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,467
I'm here, remember?

334
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:53,800
I'm the strong one for you
and your secret keeper, right?

335
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:58,033
Felma, I trust Didang.

336
00:21:58,167 --> 00:21:59,900
And it's just a few days.

337
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:01,667
It'll be the weekend soon.

338
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:04,267
And when I get back,
Emil will be with me.

339
00:22:05,667 --> 00:22:07,033
Emil?

340
00:22:07,167 --> 00:22:08,200
Who's that, Sir?

341
00:22:11,167 --> 00:22:12,933
Dr. Emil Yunque.

342
00:22:13,067 --> 00:22:14,067
My cousin.

343
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,167
He's a neurologist.

344
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:18,100
Felma's getting
a second opinion.

345
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:41,467
Dad?

346
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,400
Jeff.

347
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:49,800
Let's go home.

348
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:15,600
Book me a ticket.

349
00:23:15,733 --> 00:23:17,767
I'm coming with you
to Davao tonight.

350
00:23:23,133 --> 00:23:25,500
Attorney, they're
falsely accusing me.

351
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:27,533
Do you have proof of what
you're accusing Miss Cruz of?

352
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:28,300
That's her number.

353
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:30,833
Go on. Call it.

354
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:33,067
There. Look.

355
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:33,933
Oh my god!

356
00:23:34,067 --> 00:23:35,833
Sir Manuel, is that you?

357
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:38,067
- Welcome back...
- Dad!

358
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:40,133
Where's Felma?

359
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:43,000
Welcome to Davao, Felma.

360
00:23:43,133 --> 00:23:45,600
He talks about you all the time.

361
00:23:45,733 --> 00:23:46,467
Hello, Mom.

362
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,500
Where are you?

363
00:23:47,633 --> 00:23:49,400
I'm here in Davao.

364
00:23:49,533 --> 00:23:50,600
What?

365
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:51,767
Is that your mom?
